OOS construction: new shelling, wounded

04 Nov 2019, 08:39


On November 3, the armed forces of the Russian Federation and its mercenaries violated the ceasefire 14 times.

The enemy fired at the positions of the units of the Joint Forces with the prohibited by the Minsk agreements 82 mm mortars, as well as grenade launchers of various systems, large machine guns and other small arms, informs the headquarters of the OOS.



In the area of responsibility of the tactical group "East" the Russian occupation troops carried out 4 shelling:

near Sand and Sandstone - with RPGs and large machine guns;
not far from the Water that is on grenade launchers of different systems on the Azov;
near Pavopol - from small arms, with large machine guns including.

In the area of responsibility of the tactical group "North" recorded 10 enemy shelling:

nearby Novolugansk - small arms and machine guns anti-tank and automatic grenade launchers;
near Free Farm - with grenade launchers and small arms;
in the area of Gold (outside the breeding site) - of large caliber machine guns;
three times near Lugansk - from grenade launchers of various systems and large caliber machine guns
near Zaytsev - with LNG, small arms and automatic grenade launchers;
near the South - from large-caliber machine guns and hand-held and anti-tank grenade launchers;
near Novozanovka - automatic grenade launchers and large machine guns.

Yesterday, November 3, a gunman was wounded by gunfire.
Since the beginning of this era, armed forces of the Russian Federation and its mercenaries of rocket-propelled grenades, machine-guns and 82 mm mortars have been firing our positions near Novolugansk. There were no casualties among the Allied forces.
Earlier in the UN counted the number of casualties among civilians in the Donbass.
The UN also provided 14 tonnes of humanitarian aid to the ORDL.
